article.headline: IUPUI 75, S. Utah 60
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- Robert Glenn and Alex Young each scored 24 points to lead IUPUI to an 75-60 victory over Southern Utah Thursday night. Leroy Nobles added 12 points and Billy Pettiford 10 for the Jaguars (14-7, 7-1 Summit). The four players accounted for all but five of IUPUI's points. The Jaguars opened up a 37-19 halftime lead against the Thunderbirds (5-14, 1-7), who went just 7-for-27 (26 percent) from the field in the first half. Matt Massey had 15 points to lead Southern Utah and Ryan Brimley added 11. IUPUI outrebounded Southern Utah 37-25, led by Young's nine, and the Jaguars made 51 percent of their outside shots in the game.
